title.narrative: ENHANCED CAPACITY FOR NUTRITION GOVERNANCE AT CENTRAL AND DECENTRALIZED LEVELS

description.narrative: Enhanced capacity for nutrition governance at both central and decentralized levels, which contributes to Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children under 5, pregnant and lactating women, and adolescents have access to and utilize quality and effective nutrition services, and adopt improved nutrition practices

title.narrative: Enhanced capacity for nutrition governance at both central and decentralized levels

description.narrative: Capacity for nutrition governance was strengthened at central and decentralized level in policy development, planning and coordination to ensure effective use of resources, avoid duplication and increase synergies between interventions. This included support for the development of key national documents such as the Nutrition Policy. UNICEF has partnered with the Rwandan Parliamentary Forum (RWPF) to ensure high-level advocacy to keep nutrition at the top of national priorities. UNICEF collaboration with the Rwanda Management Institute will build district capacity on results-based planning for nutrition. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/08/2020
